    "feat": {
        "name": "Whisper on the Wind",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "subtype": "feat",
        "text": "You speak in a whisper, a soft wind carrying your words far away. This has the effect of the *message* spell with a range of 500 feet, and it can target only a creature surrounded by air. If you start your message with the target's name, you and the target don't need to be able to see each other, nor do you need line of effect.\n\n---\n\n**Level (4th)** The range is 1 mile.  \n**Level (14th)** The range is planetary plus the Plane of Air.",
        "level": 1,
        "action_type": {
            "type": "stat_block_section",
            "subtype": "action_type",
            "name": "One Action"
        },
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Air",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 5,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 452",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 452",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 452,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "8ca8a0ac0e16b3c136f09ca48d8578bb",
                "text": "Effects with the air trait either manipulate or conjure air. Those that manipulate air have no effect in a vacuum or an area without air. Creatures with this trait consist primarily of air or have a connection to magical air.   \n  \nPlanes with this trait consist mostly of open spaces and air of various levels of turbulence, though they also contain rare islands of floating stone and other elements and energies. Air planes usually have breathable atmospheres, though they might include clouds of acidic or toxic gas. Earth creatures often find themselves at a disadvantage within air planes, as there\u2019s little solid ground for them to gain their bearings, which tends to at least make them uncomfortable."
            },
            {
                "name": "Auditory",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 16,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 453",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 453",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 453,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "84c09922ddd30f2144494f2cb6f19412",
                "text": "Auditory actions and effects rely on sound. An action with the auditory trait can be successfully performed only if the creature using the action can speak or otherwise produce the required sounds. A spell or effect with the auditory trait has its effect only if the target can hear it. This applies only to sound-based parts of the effect, as determined by the GM. This is different from a sonic effect, which still affects targets who can\u2019t hear it (such as deaf targets) as long as the effect itself makes sound."
            },
            {
                "name": "Illusion",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 92,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 457",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 457",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 457,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "7a03232791db31528747d8a9f9463fd9",
                "text": "Effects and magic items with this trait involve false sensory stimuli."
            },
            {
                "name": "Impulse",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Rage of Elements",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Rage of Elements pg. 15",
                            "alt": "Rage of Elements pg. 15",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 205
                        },
                        "page": 15,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 205
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "f83779b12b3f1e7096ae9a32ca68ea4f",
                "text": "The primary magical actions kineticists use are called impulses. You can use an impulse only if your kinetic aura is active and channeling that element, and only if you have a hand free to shape the elemental flow. The impulse trait means the action has the concentrate trait unless another ability changes this. If an impulse allows you to choose an element, you can choose any element you're channeling, and the impulse gains that element's trait.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "concentrate",
                        "alt": "concentrate",
                        "game-obj": "Traits",
                        "aonid": 32
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Kineticist",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Rage of Elements",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Rage of Elements pg. 237",
                            "alt": "Rage of Elements pg. 237",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 205
                        },
                        "page": 237,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 205
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "721afce0c1e219e9edd3709db105bb4e",
                "text": "This indicates abilities from the kineticist class.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "kineticist",
                        "alt": "kineticist",
                        "game-obj": "Classes",
                        "aonid": 23
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Linguistic",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 101,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 458,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "c1c0a189dd3d1a3d7c5daf9a6bafba49",
                "text": "An effect with this trait depends on language comprehension. A linguistic effect that targets a creature works only if the target understands the language you are using."
            },
            {
                "name": "Primal",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 134,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 460",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 460",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 460,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "60a4f011afd1e0fac8211bd01108d104",
                "text": "This magic comes from the primal tradition, connecting to the natural world and instinct. Anything with this trait is magical.  \n  \nA creature with this trait is primarily constituted of or has a strong connection to primal magic."
            }
        ],
